One JUNE 1, ARC RESCUE begins our ANTI-FIREWORKS CAMPAIGN
The purpose is to EDUCATE the small but dangerous number of our neighbors and community members
who set off personal (and often illegal) Fireworks in our neighborhoods. These explosions terrify our pets,
and often babies, and often people with PTSD such as Veterans.
This is the first set of posters we encourage our neighbors to download from our website for FREE onto
regular
standard 8 1/2" by 11". Print on your home printer and post in the front yard beginning June1 through
July 31.
This is a GRASS ROOTS CAMPAIGN to help protect the most VULNERABLE in our families!
HELP PROTECT OUR BABIES, OUR PETS, AND OUR VETERANS WITH PTSD!
